****************************************************************************
     AUSTRALIAN SPEECH SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY ASSOCIATION (ASSTA)
****************************************************************************

ASSTA is pleased to announce that it is now on the WWW to offer services to
both members and non-members alike.  The Home Page is located at:

        	http://cslab.anu.edu.au/assta


and currently includes the following information and links:

*   Introduction to the Australian Speech Science and Technology
    Association provides information about the charter of the Association, 
    its committees and activities, its membership details, and a listing of 
    its Corporate Members. 
		http://cslab.anu.edu.au/assta/assta.html

*   Directory of Australian Speech Science and Technology gives information
    on groups and individuals throughout Australia who are members of the 
    Australian Speech Science & Technology Association (ASSTA). It features 
    a search facility for groups and individual members, cross-referenced 
    research interests and direct email and home-page links.
		http://ciips.ee.uwa.edu.au/assta-directory

    ASSTA members and the groups to which they belong are encouraged to
    regularly update your information as the directory provides an easy to 
    use interface to do this.

*   ASSTA is proud to have been selected to host the 5th International
    Conference on Spoken Language Processing ICSLP'98 which will be held in 
    Sydney.
		http://trust.anu.edu.au:80/icslp98

*   The ANDOSL Project is now advertising the availability of data products
    and offers background information on the project, some descriptive views 
    on the data, and ordering information.  
		http://andosl.anu.edu.au/andosl

*   Speech Science and Technology Conferences continue to be a major activity 
    of ASSTA. They are biennial and provide the principal forum for speech 
    research and technology discussion in Australia.
		http://cslab.anu.edu.au/assta/assta_sst.html
